</table><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A stylized model of hedge fund managem=
ent is that in the olden days, hedge funds started out as basically one cle=
ver investor pursuing one strategy. If it worked out, and if the manager ha=
d big aspirations, she might then hire someone else to run a different stra=
tegy within the same firm. If it worked out repeatedly over time, eventuall=
y the manager would supervise 100 other managers running 100 strategies, an=
d her job would be not =E2=80=9Cclever investor=E2=80=9D but rather =E2=80=
=9Cbuilder of institutions, developer of talent and allocator of capital am=
ong strategies.=E2=80=9D=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And then the=
