i scheme. The trick is that he pitched the Ponzi scheme to other Harvard MB=
As, who thought =E2=80=9Cwell that guy can=E2=80=99t be running a Ponzi sch=
eme, he=E2=80=99s got a Harvard MBA.=E2=80=9D In some ways, a=C2=A0genius m=
ove, though arguably <em>most=C2=A0</em>Harvard MBAs find career paths that=
 are both more lucrative and more legal.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Th=
at paragraph I quoted is from Jen Wieczner=E2=80=99s <a href=3D"https://lin=
k.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/36001625.196409/aHR0cHM6Ly9ueW1hZy5jb20v=
aW50ZWxsaWdlbmNlci9hcnRpY2xlL2luc2lkZS10aGUtaGFydmFyZC1idXNpbmVzcy1zY2hvb2w=
tcG9uemktc2NoZW1lLmh0bWw/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB0ac81a3c" itemprop=3D"Sto=
ryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; =
text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-c=
olor: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">New Yor=
k Magazine</a> story about Artamonov, which adds the crucial information th=
at he didn=E2=80=99t=C2=A0<em>just=C2=A0</em>have a Harvard MBA; he also wo=
rked at Greenlight, so it was extra-weird that he=E2=80=99d get into the Po=
nzi business:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">As the months pas=
sed, the friend reached out to someone he knew who had also invested with A=
rtamonov and voiced what seemed like a crazy, irrational fear. =E2=80=9CThe=
re=E2=80=99s no way Vlad would be running a Ponzi scheme, right?=E2=80=9D h=
e asked. The two dismissed it from their minds. =E2=80=9CWhy would he risk =
his reputation? It=E2=80=99s a small amount of money, it=E2=80=99s not rati=
onal =E2=80=94 why would he put his career on the line?=E2=80=9D they reaso=
ned. =E2=80=9CI think you give a friend the benefit of the doubt.=E2=80=9D<=
/p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I am not sure that there=E2=80=
=99s a satisfying answer to that question, but the article does hint that A=
rtamonov was successful early =E2=80=94=C2=A0HBS, Greenlight, expensive Ham=
ptons summers =E2=80=94=C2=A0but it didn=E2=80=99t last: He left Greenlight=
 to start his own fund, it =E2=80=9Cwas not a huge success,=E2=80=9D and he=
 was downwardly mobile and nostalgic for his time at Greenlight. If you hav=
e expensive tastes, no money, and a nostalgia for the time when you were yo=
ung and promising and just starting out in a fancy profession, I suppose th=
at is how you end up starting a Harvard Business School Ponzi scheme.</p><t=
able class=3D"header" width=3D"100%" border=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" cellpad=
